1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:26,000
Such a strong spirit is worthy
of being the wife of Bandit Yai.

2
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:28,160
If you want Pinanong to be your wife…

3
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:30,000
you have to kill him with your own hands.

4
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:31,520
I'll give him to you.

5
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:39,640
<i>This is the last thing</i>
<i>I can do for you, Pin.</i>

6
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:41,960
I want to see your face one last time

7
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:44,280
before I lose the chance
to ever see you again.

8
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,400
You'll be okay. We have to stay together.

9
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:48,640
Pin. Pin!

10
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:53,320
Hey, can you tell me now

11
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,960
why you brought us here?

12
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,000
Or is it about the money?

13
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,480
Let me and my children go,

14
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,000
and I'll get you the money.

15
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:08,880
Children?

16
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:13,920
Or… Oh, were you a worker at Paisal Farm

17
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,840
who got angry for getting fired?

18
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:18,880
How could I be angry at my dear lover?

19
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,480
Teera.

20
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,960
You're still alive.

21
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:33,280
I thought Mr. Tong had already killed you.

22
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:36,400
I'm so glad you're still alive.

23
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:43,760
Is that so?

24
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:47,760
Because I remember
you didn't care about me at all.

25
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:49,320
You let him drag me away to kill me.

26
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:55,800
But it seems my time
to die hadn't come yet.

27
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:58,000
Jerd and Kan came and saved me in time.

28
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:01,560
I had to stay in treatment for so long

29
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,320
that I almost became disabled.

30
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:08,080
Calm down, Teera. Listen to me first.

31
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:23,920
How is my son, Doctor?

32
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,120
He's out of the danger zone now.

33
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,840
Luckily, the bullet didn't hit
any vital organs.

34
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:33,680
Most importantly, the patient
is strong and has a strong will to live.

35
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,440
Congratulations.

36
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:36,440
Thank you so much.

37
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,080
Jom.

38
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:47,320
Then I'll go check on Pin.

39
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,320
Alright.

40
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:49,840
Jom.

41
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,040
Hey.

42
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:03,600
Do you want to wear
your shoes out from pacing?

43
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,520
Sit down.

44
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:07,080
What if something happens to Pin?

45
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,640
And what could you do about it?

46
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,520
That's why I told you to sit down

47
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,920
and think through everything
that's happened.

48
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:15,960
It's my fault.

49
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,880
It's all because of me
that Pin ended up like this.

50
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:23,120
This is a lesson no one can teach you.

51
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,920
You have to get through it yourself.

52
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,320
Mr. Yai.

53
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,560
Uncle Pload.

54
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:36,080
Yes, Mr. Yai.

55
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,000
It's alright now.

56
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:47,960
How is Pinanong?

57
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,240
We don't know yet.

58
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:52,720
The bullet is still inside her.
The doctor is operating now.

59
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:55,760
Uncle Pload,
were you able to catch Madam Krongsuk?

60
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,680
They escaped.

61
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:01,600
Someone helped them. But don't worry.

62
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:04,520
The police are chasing them now.

63
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,360
I already told him.

64
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,600
Uncle Pload…

65
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:17,000
I'm sorry I couldn't save Aunt Pen.

66
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:19,480
- I'm really sorry.
- Mr. Yai,

67
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,440
it's my fault.

68
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:25,960
You and Pan

69
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,800
must never blame yourselves.

70
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:29,960
Otherwise,

71
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:33,120
your Aunt Pen would be heartbroken.

72
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,280
Uncle Pload.

73
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:52,000
This is the village chief
who helped us many times.

74
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,960
Thank you very much, Village Chief.

75
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,480
<i>Help…</i>

76
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:01,800
<i>Teera is going to kill us.</i>

77
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:05,200
So the one
who helped Krongsuk escape was Teera.

78
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,120
He must be seeking revenge.

79
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,440
Tatsanee says he's going to kill everyone.

80
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,960
I'm going to help Nee.

81
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:15,480
The location she sent isn't far from here.

82
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,600
Pan, don't go.

83
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,200
Have you forgotten?

84
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:28,080
Her mother killed your Aunt Pen.

85
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:30,120
But Nee helped us, Dad.

86
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:33,440
If it weren't for her,
your name might never have been cleared.

87
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,360
Uncle Pload,

88
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:38,800
if anything happens to Tatsanee,
Pin will never forgive me.

89
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,320
I'm going with you.

90
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:47,840
Mr. Yai.

91
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,960
I can't let Nee die.

92
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:52,640
This is the only chance I have
to fix anything.

93
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:54,320
Please take care of Pin for me.

94
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:57,400
- Mr. Yai.
- Pan, call the police.

95
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:02,120
- Mr. Yai.
- I'm going.

96
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:06,840
If he's determined to go,
even an elephant couldn't hold him back.

97
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,120
Isn't that right?

98
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:15,080
Mr. Tong forced me.

99
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:18,320
He threatened to hurt my children.

100
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,760
I had no choice.

101
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,200
If you love your children so much,

102
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:25,960
then I'll send them to Heaven first.

103
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,280
No. Don't shoot.

104
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,960
Don't shoot, Teera.

105
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:32,760
If you shoot me, you'll go to prison.

106
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:35,400
But if you let me go,

107
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:38,720
I'll take you to the jewelry I hid.

108
00:08:38,799 --> 00:08:40,520
I'll give it all to you.

109
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:47,600
Teera.

110
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,560
I love you so much.

111
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:57,280
Don't you remember
the times we were happy together?

112
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:19,480
Stop lying. You never loved me.

113
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,440
You never valued my loyalty.

114
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:26,040
I was nothing more
than a dog you kept around.

115
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,080
But I'll give you a choice.

116
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:36,160
Out of these two, only one will survive.

117
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:39,720
Choose. Now!

118
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,840
Choose!

119
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:53,800
Or I'll shoot both of them.

120
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,560
Auntie.

121
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:06,560
Take Nee and go.

122
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:09,320
I already want to die.

123
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,320
No. No.

124
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:14,120
How could I watch you die? No.

125
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,960
No, Na.

126
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,800
We have to get out of here together.

127
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,360
- No.
- Hurry! I'll count to three.

128
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,440
One.

129
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:25,200
Two.

130
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:09,200
No, Auntie. Let go.

131
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:12,320
- Let go of me. Let go!
- No.

132
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:14,120
- Nee! Let go of me, Auntie!
- No.

133
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,440
Let go!

134
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:18,120
Nee! Auntie!

135
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,240
No! Take me instead!

136
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:25,240
No! Let go!

137
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,160
No.

138
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:54,040
Auntie!

139
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,160
Hey!

140
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:10,800
Mom! Mom!

141
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:15,720
Hey, Kan.

142
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:18,080
Police. The police are here. Let's go.

143
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:26,440
Stop! Police! Drop your weapons!

144
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,440
Kan, shoot to open a path!

145
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,280
Don't run!

146
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:43,400
Boss, run.

147
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,320
Jerd!

148
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:48,600
Kan!

149
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,400
Clear.

150
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:06,120
Go after them. Search everywhere.

151
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:10,800
Drop the weapon. Hands up.

152
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:14,360
Sergeant, search the car.

153
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:30,280
- Mom.
- Mom.

154
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,280
I'm sorry.

155
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:42,600
I almost

156
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:47,480
got Paisal Farm for you, Na.

157
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:51,720
I never wanted it.

158
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,520
I just wanted you.

159
00:13:57,760 --> 00:13:59,880
I wanted my mother more.

160
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,200
Auntie…

161
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:17,440
Why didn't you just let me die?

162
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,600
Why are you wasting time? Move.

163
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:36,760
I'll carry her to the hospital myself.

164
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:40,680
No. I don't want your help. No!

165
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:42,680
Auntie, Mr. Yai is trying to help you.

166
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:44,960
You need to go to the hospital.

167
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:48,440
Auntie.

168
00:14:57,840 --> 00:15:00,720
Remember this.

169
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:04,640
I never didn't love you.

170
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:10,320
I never wanted you to die.

171
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:14,360
I…

172
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:17,040
I just wanted to hear you

173
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,840
call me Mom just once.

174
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:33,720
Mom.

175
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,920
Mom!

176
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,240
Mom! Mom!

177
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,960
- Mom!
- Mom!

178
00:15:56,240 --> 00:16:00,160
Help. Mom! Mom!

179
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:04,320
- Mom!
- Help her. Please help her.

180
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:14,160
Doctor.

181
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:18,080
Doctor, how is my in-law?

182
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:20,320
Both mother and child are safe.

183
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:22,080
But she hasn't regained consciousness yet.

184
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:28,200
Child? Whose child?

185
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:31,280
You're the husband.

186
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:33,800
Didn't you know
your wife is two months pregnant?

187
00:16:34,760 --> 00:16:37,600
- Excuse me.
- Right. Thank you.

188
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,920
Pin is pregnant? Why didn't I know?

189
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:43,400
Maybe she didn't know
she was pregnant either.

190
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:50,440
Mr. Yai, were the police

191
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:53,400
able to capture Madam Krongsuk?

192
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,720
Madam was shot dead by Teera.

193
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:57,960
But Nee and Na are safe.

194
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:00,040
They're giving their statements
to the police now.

195
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:06,400
Then, I forgive everything and everyone.

196
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:11,000
Let all our karma end in this life.

197
00:17:30,280 --> 00:17:31,200
Pin.

198
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,400
Please wake up soon.

199
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:39,360
I have good news to tell you.

200
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,120
Yai.

201
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:59,400
Ms. Jin found this in Pin's bag
when she arrived at the hospital.

202
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:06,280
Isn't this the model
your father used to make as a hobby?

203
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,960
Pin probably kept it for you.

204
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:15,840
I don't want anything from him!

205
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,760
Yai, look.

206
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:32,840
It was hidden inside the model.

207
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:50,360
<i>I, Paisal Thamrongrat,</i>

208
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:53,480
<i>hereby grant all my assets,</i>

209
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:56,760
<i>both present and future,</i>

210
00:18:56,840 --> 00:19:00,440
<i>including 2,420 rai of land,</i>

211
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:03,520
<i>houses, and all money in the bank,</i>

212
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:06,880
<i>to my only son,</i>

213
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:09,520
<i>Mr. Chalit Thamrongrat.</i>

214
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:14,760
<i>I miss you so much.</i>

215
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:16,920
<i>Can you forgive me?</i>

216
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:20,440
<i>I love you, Yai.</i>

217
00:19:32,520 --> 00:19:33,680
You once told me

218
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:37,800
he often talked about me.

219
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:42,200
But I didn't believe you.

220
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,560
You never lied to me, Pin.

221
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:51,000
I was just a foolish son.

222
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:05,040
Mr. Yai.

223
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:08,840
Pin.

224
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,640
We're going to have a child together.

225
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:25,120
What are you talking about?

226
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:28,200
The doctor said

227
00:20:30,560 --> 00:20:31,880
you're pregnant.

228
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:07,240
Mr. Yai…

229
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:12,640
What about Jom?

230
00:21:14,320 --> 00:21:15,880
How is he?

231
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:33,000
I don't know what to say to you, Jom.

232
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:49,560
If you want to punch me to get revenge,

233
00:21:50,360 --> 00:21:51,600
go ahead.

234
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,360
You can punch my nose

235
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:01,640
or my chin.

236
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:03,960
I know you still have plenty of strength.

237
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:41,160
I've wronged you many times.

238
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:46,440
I nearly caused your death.

239
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,840
I was foolish and arrogant.

240
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:54,080
Please forgive me.

241
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:03,920
You weren't foolish.

242
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:09,280
Your heart is just incredible.

243
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,680
Pin and I owe you our lives.

244
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:40,960
With all this time I took to return
and arrange your funeral,

245
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:44,120
I made you wait far too long.

246
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:45,200
I'm sorry, Pen.

247
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:47,640
I've been a useless husband.

248
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:51,280
If we meet again in the next life,

249
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:53,360
please give me another chance
to make things right.

250
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:07,520
What, Dad? Is there something on my face?

251
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,760
You've grown up a lot, Pan.

252
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:15,800
You're praising me

253
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:18,040
for helping Yai clear the charge
of evading arrest

254
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:20,000
and helping you reduce your sentence

255
00:24:20,080 --> 00:24:22,560
to probation?

256
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:26,520
Yeah. You're amazing.

257
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:28,640
Dad.

258
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:32,200
You're praising me. Make it sound sweet.

259
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,720
That didn't sound sincere at all.

260
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:35,320
Hey.

261
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:40,120
You know this is how I talk.

262
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:45,200
If you won't say it, I will.

263
00:24:45,280 --> 00:24:46,440
I love you, Dad.

264
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:48,880
- I love you the most.
- Pan, what are you doing?

265
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:51,800
- That tickles. Let go.
- If you won't say you love me,

266
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:53,960
I won't let go!

267
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:55,760
- I love you.
- Hey, Pan.

268
00:24:55,840 --> 00:24:57,800
It's embarrassing. Let go.

269
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:04,040
Pan.

270
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:11,080
No father

271
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:13,120
loves someone else's child

272
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:16,400
more than his own.

273
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:18,280
Come here.

274
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:24,640
Yes, Dad.

275
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:28,760
Let's go.

276
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:33,240
Dad. It took you so long.

277
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:06,920
- Here they are.
- Hello.

278
00:26:09,440 --> 00:26:11,320
- Pin.
- Pin.

279
00:26:14,720 --> 00:26:16,200
Welcome back home, Pin.

280
00:26:17,040 --> 00:26:18,320
Hello, everyone.

281
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,120
Why are you doing that us?

282
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,240
You don't have to.

283
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:23,200
Of course, I have to.

284
00:26:23,280 --> 00:26:25,600
I owe you all a lot.

285
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:29,920
Uncle Tawin, Waan, and Noi.

286
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:38,920
Pin.

287
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:42,320
Jom asked me to give this to you.

288
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:07,080
<i>I'll never forget the time we shared.</i>

289
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:09,120
<i>Your smile</i>

290
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:11,440
<i>will keep smiling in my heart</i>

291
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:14,040
<i>for as long as I still breathe.</i>

292
00:27:26,920 --> 00:27:29,040
<i>I hope you and Mr. Yai will be happy.</i>

293
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:31,880
<i>Let me say this, Pin,</i>

294
00:27:32,680 --> 00:27:34,800
<i>even though I know</i>
<i>I probably have no right to.</i>

295
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:36,520
<i>I love you.</i>

296
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:13,120
No wonder

297
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:16,600
Jom deleted his LINE
and blocked my number completely.

298
00:28:18,280 --> 00:28:19,880
He probably wants
to cut things off completely.

299
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:22,320
You have to give him time.

300
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:30,360
Mr. Na.

301
00:28:31,840 --> 00:28:33,360
Where are you going?

302
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:36,520
Na already found a rental house, Pin.

303
00:28:46,720 --> 00:28:47,800
I need a word with you.

304
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:16,120
You can stay here if you want to.

305
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:28,880
I hate this place.

306
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:33,720
I'll take my leave now.

307
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,080
I'm sorry.

308
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,240
Everything started
because of my own jealousy.

309
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:51,360
I was afraid I'd lose my father
to you and his new wife.

310
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:56,480
I hated your mother, and I ended up
taking it out on you and Tatsanee too.

311
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:01,920
I'm the one

312
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:04,800
who was even worse than you.

313
00:30:05,960 --> 00:30:08,880
I framed you
so Uncle Paisal would love me.

314
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:13,720
I don't even deserve your forgiveness.

315
00:30:14,640 --> 00:30:16,560
We can start over, can't we?

316
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:18,840
This farm still needs you and Tatsanee.

317
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:20,840
I can't manage it alone.

318
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:33,640
Someday,

319
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:37,440
I may get the chance
to come back and help you.

320
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:41,960
But today is not that day.

321
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:08,560
Hey, where are you going?

322
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:11,560
I'm going somewhere else.

323
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:13,520
Maybe I'll find a job in Bangkok.

324
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:15,600
You could stay here.

325
00:31:16,120 --> 00:31:18,120
Yai wants you to stay too.

326
00:31:19,080 --> 00:31:21,880
What about you? Do you want me to stay?

327
00:31:23,240 --> 00:31:25,360
If you stayed, that'd be good.

328
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:27,040
You could help Yai with the work.

329
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:31,360
Stop using Mr. Yai as an excuse.

330
00:31:33,320 --> 00:31:35,840
How do you really feel about me?

331
00:31:36,600 --> 00:31:37,600
That's what I want to know.

332
00:31:43,560 --> 00:31:44,480
I…

333
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:47,160
I don't really know how to start.

334
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:49,880
We've been friends
since we were kids, right?

335
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:51,600
We grew up together.

336
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:54,360
And now, we've met again here.

337
00:31:54,960 --> 00:31:56,840
- I…
- So?

338
00:31:58,240 --> 00:32:01,560
We've fought sometimes,
hated each other sometimes, like normal.

339
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:05,400
But lately, I think

340
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:07,960
we've been talking more nicely.

341
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:12,880
So maybe
we'll just keep talking like this.

342
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:15,840
I don't want to waste time.

343
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:17,480
I'm single right now.

344
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:19,880
You want to be my boyfriend?

345
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:23,080
That'd be nice… Hey!

346
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:25,240
What did you say?

347
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:39,560
Those two always fought
and still ended up together, just like us.

348
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:41,680
They've been fighting
since we all were kids.

349
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:44,520
I never fought with you.

350
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:47,080
You were the one
who always liked to tease me.

351
00:32:47,880 --> 00:32:50,080
Because I wanted you to talk to me.

352
00:32:50,160 --> 00:32:52,680
I wanted you to pay attention to me.
That's why I always teased you.

353
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:55,400
Isn't that right, my child?

354
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:58,400
Your mom has never been able
to keep up with anyone.

355
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:03,120
The person
I'm still worried about is Mr. Na.

356
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:06,880
I want him to go back to Ms. On.

357
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,520
Let him choose for himself.

358
00:33:35,600 --> 00:33:36,440
On.

359
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:45,200
I came to apologize to you.

360
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:53,520
I want to ask you…

361
00:33:58,520 --> 00:34:00,680
to give me a chance to make it right.

362
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:19,440
I'm strong enough now.

363
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:26,120
I want to move forward

364
00:34:26,719 --> 00:34:29,840
and begin a new life
with someone who truly loves me.

365
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:37,120
But that person may not be you.

366
00:35:29,160 --> 00:35:32,120
Did you call
the livestock office for help?

367
00:35:35,160 --> 00:35:36,720
Hey, Jom.

368
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:40,120
Why are you here?

369
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:41,880
Jin.

370
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:44,960
I'm running a farm here now.

371
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:49,360
Dad gave all his savings to me,
so I started a small farm here.

372
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:51,520
- The world is so incredibly small.
- Yeah.

373
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:52,960
I just moved here too.

374
00:35:53,040 --> 00:35:53,960
Really?

375
00:35:54,480 --> 00:35:55,480
Yeah.

376
00:35:56,360 --> 00:35:59,200
So, what's wrong with the buffalo?

377
00:36:01,080 --> 00:36:02,760
It hasn't been eating much grass.

378
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:05,000
And it looks kind of tense.

379
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:07,160
Then let me take a look.

380
00:36:08,120 --> 00:36:09,800
Let me see.

381
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:13,040
I think it might have a fever.

382
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:42,880
My cow
seems to have something wrong too.

383
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:44,200
It doesn't look very well.

384
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:47,920
- Could you go check it for me too?
- Sure.

385
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:50,160
- Let's go.
- This way.

386
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:07,280
THE SHEPHERD BOY

387
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:26,320
Mr. Yai, make Thungya stop crying, please.

388
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:28,120
Don't cry, baby.

389
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:30,200
Your mom is scolding me again. See?

390
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:32,600
There, there. Stay still.

391
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:34,160
You're always pushing me.

392
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:39,720
- There, there.
- Phukhao.

393
00:37:39,800 --> 00:37:41,720
- Sleep, baby.
- Phukhao.

394
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:45,520
Mr. Yai, Phukhao is crying now.

395
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:47,640
Did you give him water?

396
00:37:47,720 --> 00:37:49,840
I told you not to forget.

397
00:37:51,080 --> 00:37:52,840
Noi, where did you go?

398
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:54,720
Noi! Noi!

399
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:56,240
- I'm here.
- Just a sec.

400
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:58,520
- I'm here, Mr. Yai.
- Flip back over here.

401
00:37:58,600 --> 00:38:00,280
I went to warm the milk.

402
00:38:05,560 --> 00:38:08,680
- Water, please. Phukhao, don't cry.
- Sure.

403
00:38:09,280 --> 00:38:11,800
- He won't stop crying.
- Come on. Up.

404
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:14,160
- Here I am. Here, here.
- Don't cry.

405
00:38:14,240 --> 00:38:15,840
Come on, Phukhao. Drink some water.

406
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:18,240
Drink water. Go ahead.

407
00:38:19,240 --> 00:38:21,280
Don't cry, baby.

408
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:23,880
It's already three in the morning.
I still haven't slept yet.

409
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:25,840
- There, there.
- Mr. Yai,

410
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:27,200
don't scold him.

411
00:38:27,280 --> 00:38:28,520
He'll end up with issues.

412
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:31,000
I'm not scolding him.

413
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:35,320
Look. Your mom is the one
scolding me, right?

414
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:39,040
There, there. Don't cry. Have some water.

415
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:40,440
There, there.

416
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:42,640
Farm.

417
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:44,760
Mr. Yai,

418
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:46,480
Farm peed again.

419
00:38:47,760 --> 00:38:49,280
Can you get me a diaper?

420
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:51,080
Where are the diapers?

421
00:38:52,080 --> 00:38:54,360
On the table. Stacked in the basket.

422
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:59,640
- Did you get the diaper?
- Here it is.

423
00:38:59,720 --> 00:39:01,080
Okay.

424
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:04,600
Mr. Yai, take off
the adhesive strips first.

425
00:39:04,680 --> 00:39:06,680
You've done this so many times already.
How can you still forget?

426
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:09,480
I didn't forget. I thought
you were going to take them off yourself.

427
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:10,920
Don't argue.

428
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:12,920
I'm not arguing. I'm just explaining…

429
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:17,040
Alright. I'll help. There, there.

430
00:39:17,120 --> 00:39:18,600
- There, there.
- Wait a little bit more.

431
00:39:18,680 --> 00:39:20,680
- Wait a sec.
- There, there.

432
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:21,880
Here, here.

433
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:24,800
- Noi, come help over here.
- Okay.

434
00:39:30,120 --> 00:39:31,160
Daddy's coming.

435
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:36,160
- Mr. Yai.
- Mr. Yai.

436
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:38,320
- One moment.
- Oh, my. Lie down first.

437
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:41,680
- Mr. Yai.
- He hasn't eaten anything since morning.

438
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:45,720
I'm terrible.
I didn't take care of you at all.

439
00:39:46,400 --> 00:39:49,800
- Mr. Yai.
- I'm alright, Pin.

440
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:52,240
Mr. Yai.

441
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:57,240
My children.

442
00:40:01,720 --> 00:40:03,840
My little triplets.

443
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:06,360
Are you worried about Daddy?

444
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:10,640
Mr. Yai, eat your porridge first,

445
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:12,000
or you'll faint again.

446
00:40:12,600 --> 00:40:15,040
Later, dear.
The babies will fall asleep soon.

447
00:40:15,120 --> 00:40:17,640
- But--
- I'm fine. Come sit.

448
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:23,680
Among Phukhao, Thungya,

449
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:26,200
and Farm, which one of them
looks most like me?

450
00:40:31,040 --> 00:40:32,560
None of them.

451
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:35,040
They all look like me.

452
00:40:36,440 --> 00:40:39,640
That's too much. We need someone to judge.

453
00:40:39,720 --> 00:40:41,240
Alright.

454
00:40:53,320 --> 00:40:55,680
It's obvious. Why even ask?

455
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:59,920
They don't look like you at all.

456
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:03,080
But luckily, they look like their mom.

457
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:05,680
Mr. Yai,

458
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:09,680
I think the triplets look like me.

459
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:10,880
Oh, please, Dad.

460
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:12,200
That's obviously not true.

461
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:14,440
Look at their eyes, noses, and mouths.

462
00:41:14,520 --> 00:41:16,280
They clearly look just like me
when I was little.

463
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:17,400
Pan,

464
00:41:17,480 --> 00:41:22,600
since when were you a blood relative
of Mr. Yai in a past life?

465
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:24,680
Oh? And what about you?

466
00:41:24,760 --> 00:41:26,760
Is Mr. Yai your secret son or something?

467
00:41:31,480 --> 00:41:35,640
I think they look like both you and Pin,
a mix of both.

468
00:41:36,480 --> 00:41:38,360
<i>That answer is acceptable.</i>

469
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:43,480
<i>Ms. Nee, didn't you say you were going</i>
<i>to come help take care of the babies?</i>

470
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:47,200
I want to, but

471
00:41:47,280 --> 00:41:50,400
I can't go right now. I feel nauseous.

472
00:41:53,480 --> 00:41:54,960
I'm going to have a baby.

473
00:41:55,040 --> 00:41:57,040
I'm going to beat you with quadruplets.

474
00:41:57,720 --> 00:41:59,960
Pan, stop boasting…

475
00:42:00,040 --> 00:42:03,560
…and go look after your wife
before she falls over. Go.

476
00:42:03,640 --> 00:42:05,200
I gotta go now. See you.

477
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:10,240
Mr. Yai, I gotta go now.

478
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:12,200
I have an appointment with the monk.

479
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:14,840
I'm going to ask him
for some cool names for my grandchild.

480
00:42:18,160 --> 00:42:19,480
Uncle Pload is crazy about his grandchild.

481
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:21,360
He must've fully accepted Nee by now.

482
00:42:21,440 --> 00:42:23,920
Children really do bring
happiness to a family.

483
00:42:25,240 --> 00:42:27,880
If they grow up to be kind

484
00:42:27,960 --> 00:42:31,320
and gentle and never hurt anyone,

485
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:34,600
then we can say
we've fulfilled our duty as parents.

486
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:41,920
But you still haven't
fulfilled your duty as a wife.

487
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:44,560
Ever since you got pregnant until today,

488
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:46,800
I've gone to bed wilted
every single night.

489
00:42:46,880 --> 00:42:49,280
So tonight…

490
00:42:50,480 --> 00:42:51,800
I'm not ready yet.

491
00:42:51,880 --> 00:42:54,080
Why not? The babies will be asleep soon.

492
00:42:55,280 --> 00:42:57,640
I have to pump milk for them every day.

493
00:42:57,720 --> 00:42:59,360
Do you know how sore that makes me?

494
00:42:59,440 --> 00:43:02,320
Great. Then I will massage them for you.
Come here.

495
00:43:03,360 --> 00:43:05,080
No, Mr. Yai.

496
00:43:05,800 --> 00:43:07,920
Why not? I will help you with the pumping.
I guarantee

497
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:11,040
- one night and your soreness will be gone.
- No, Mr. Yai.

498
00:43:11,120 --> 00:43:14,760
- Mr. Yai, you're so naughty.
- I just want to hold my wife.

499
00:43:15,800 --> 00:43:18,920
Mr. Yai. It tickles.

500
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:21,360
It tickles. Enough.

501
00:43:44,080 --> 00:43:47,320
My children. There, there.

502
00:45:24,920 --> 00:45:31,000
THE END

503
00:45:59,920 --> 00:46:02,320
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
